notesStmt.note: Effaced owner's statement (f. 451v); partially removed bookplate with the initials MLP [?] (inside back cover).

msContents.summary: Collection of romantic tales in Persian derived from Indian sources. Large areas of text pasted over between f. 405 and 414.

supportDesc.extent: 451 leaves : 240 x 150 (180 x 100) mm, bound to 235 x 155 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Bound in red leather over pasteboard with flap; blind stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis, four thin, radial lines and frame made up of blind tooled dots.

origin.p: Item is undated; probably copied in the 18th century in India.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Alexander Isaac Cotheal (stamp f. 2r, 451v, second to last flyleaf verso).
